  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_system": "The core of the computation subsystem",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_system_desc.0": "The computation subsystem introduces virtual Crafting Processors (vCPUs):",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_system_desc.1": "The host provides only one vCPU to the ME network at a time, with capacity equal to all currently available bytes in the subsystem",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_system_desc.2": "When a user assigns a crafting task to a vCPU, the host automatically adjusts the vCPU's byte allocation to the task's requirements before assigning it to a Threading Core",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_system_desc.3": "New vCPUs can be allocated continuously until the total allocated vCPUs reach the max thread count",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_system_desc.4": "vCPUs are immediately destroyed when the crafting task completes and all items are returned",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_threading_core.0": "Threading Core is the main part of the computation subsystem, providing thread count to the host controller",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_threading_core.1": "Threads determine the maximum virtual CPUs for the computation subsystem",
  "tooltip.neoecoae.computation_threading_core.2": "When destroyed, compressed CPU data will be directly saved to the dropped item",
